{"title_page": "Miss Universe Albania", "text_new": "{{use mdy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox organization\n|name         = Miss Universe Albania Organization\n|motto        = Perzgjedhja e Miss Universe Albania\n|formation    = 2002\n|type         = [[Beauty pageant]]\n|headquarters = [[Tirana]]\n|location     = [[Albania]]\n|membership   = [[Miss Universe]]<br>[[Miss World]]\n|language     = [[Albanian language|Albanian]]\n|leader_title = Director\n|leader_name  = Labinot G. Sashi\n|key_people   = Eduart Deda\n|website      = {{URL|revistavip.club}}\n}}\n\n'''Miss Universe Albania''' is a national [[beauty pageant]] in [[Albania]]. The pageant was founded as Miss Albania in 2002, until rebranding as Miss Universe Albania in 2006. Since 2006, winners of the competition have competed internationally in [[Miss Universe]], while some runners-up have competed in [[Miss World]].\n\n==History==\n[[File:Lola2.jpeg|thumb|230px|[[Floriana Garo]] represented Albania in the Miss World 2012 beauty pageant.]]\nAlbania debuted at Miss Universe in 2002 with the Miss Albania organization as the official franchise holder. The organization held national pageant yearly up into 2006. Beginning in 2007, the franchise license was given to the then official photographer of Miss Universe, Fadil Berisha who happened to be from Albania. At this point Fadil created the \"Miss Universe Albania\" organization and would held occasional yearly national pageant or in some cases, designate a participant to represent Albania at Miss Universe. Fadil would continue to be the national director until 2013.\n\nIn 2014 Eduart Deda acquired the Miss Universe franchise license in Albania and consequently also the [[Miss World]] franchise license. The company would held yearly national pageants where two winners were crowned to compete at Miss Universe and Miss World. The company would held the license of Miss World until 2017.\n\nIn 2018, the Miss World license was given to Vera Grabocka who was previously the national director of Miss World in Albania between 2006-2013,  while Eduart Deda only held the Miss Universe license.\n\n==Implementation and complaints==\nThe beauty contests are carried out by two different organizers: Vera Grabocka has been competing in the Miss Albania competition since 1991, and Petri Bozo and his Deliart Club have held the Miss Shqiperia elections important. Politically, Petri Bozo is associated with the Socialist Party, Vera Grabocka with the Democratic Party. The finalists take part in the election for Miss Europe, since 2002 also for Miss World and Miss Universe.\n\n[[Albanians]] from [[Kosovo]] can also be eliminated at the Miss Albania competition: Venera Mustafa became Miss Kosovo and Miss Albania in 1999. In the same year she participated for Albania and the Miss Europe election. [[Agnesa Vuthaj]] was a member of the Miss Kosovo in 2003, a member of the Miss Albania in 2004 and a candidate as a member of the Miss World in 2004 and the Miss Universe in 2005.\n\nMiss Universe Albania was launched in 2002 to become a participant in the Miss Universe international competition.\n\nEnkeleid Omi and his agency Alba-Media have been leading the competition for Miss Earth Albania, its winners and Miss Earth since 2005. Here too, all Albanians from Kosovo stand as candidates: The 2007 winner, Shpresa Vitia, stuck from there.\n\n==Titleholders==\n[[File:Angela-martini-profile.jpg|220px|thumb|right|[[Angela Martini]], Miss Universe Albania 2010]]\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n!width=\"60\"|Year||width=\"250\"|Miss Universe Albania||width=\"100\"|Municipality\n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 2006|2006]]\n| [[Eralda Hitaj]]<ref name=albania2006>{{cite web |title=Eralda Hitaj |url=http://www.missuniverse.com/delegates/2006/files/AL.html |publisher=missuniverse.com |date=July 1, 2006 |accessdate=March 3, 2011 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060701175802/http://www.missuniverse.com/delegates/2006/files/AL.html |archivedate=July 1, 2006}}</ref>\n| [[Tirana]]\n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 2007|2007]]\n| [[Sadina Alla]]<ref name=albania2007>{{cite news |title=Miss Universe Presentation Show Gowns |url=http://www.seattlepi.com/ae/missuniverse/popup.asp?gtitle=Miss%20Universe%20Presentation%20Show%20Gowns&SubID=2553&page=0&css=/photos/fashion.css |work=[[Seattle Post-Intelligencer]] |date=May 23, 2007|accessdate=March 3, 2011 }} {{Dead link|date=December 2011|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref>\n| [[Tirana]]\n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 2008|2008]]\n| Matilda Mecini<ref name=albania2008>{{cite web |title=Beauties will attend Miss Universe 2008 |url=http://translate.googleusercontent.com/translate_c?hl=en&ie=UTF-8&sl=vi&tl=en&u=http://www.xaluan.com/modules.php%3Fname%3DNews%26file%3Darticle%26sid%3D43162&prev=_t&rurl=translate.google.com&usg=ALkJrhjkflaoLkq7H3nVoW-S-Gm2P2FlLw |publisher=xaluan.com |date=April 7, 2008 |accessdate=March 3, 2011}}</ref>\n| [[Tirana]]\n|- \n| [[Miss Universe 2009|2009]]\n| [[Hasna Xhuki\u00e7i]]<ref name=albania2009>{{cite news |title=Miss Universe bikini photos |url=http://www.torontosun.com/life/2009/08/04/10372971.html |newspaper=[[Toronto Sun]] |date=August 5, 2009 |accessdate=March 3, 2011}}</ref>\n| [[Fier County|Fier]] \n|- \n| [[Miss Universe 2010|2010]]\n| [[Angela Martini]]<ref name=albania2010>{{cite news |title=Is Angela as beautiful as Linda? |url=https://translate.google.com/translate?hl=en&sl=de&tl=en&u=http://www.20min.ch/people/schweiz/story/24458584 |newspaper=[[20 Minuten]] |date=July 19, 2010 |accessdate=March 3, 2011}}</ref>\n| [[Shkod\u00ebr County|Shkod\u00ebr]] \n|-\n| [[Miss Universe 2011|2011]]\n| [[Xhesika Berberi]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://globalbeauties.com/blog/2011/06/miss-universe-albania-2011/|title=Global Beauties - Miss Universe Albania 2011|work=Global Beauties|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151227073313/http://www.globalbeauties.com/blog/2011/06/miss-universe-albania-2011/|archivedate=December 27, 2015|df